# ============================================
# Configuration Notes
# ============================================

# Tool Configuration Options:
#   command           - Full path to executable (required)
#   description       - Human-readable description
#   autostart         - Start with framework (yes/no)
#   restart_on_crash  - Auto-restart if crashes (yes/no)
#   max_restarts      - Max restart attempts (0 = unlimited)
#   subscribe_to      - Comma-separated event types

# Event Subscriptions:
#   subscribe_to = EVENT1,EVENT2,EVENT3
#   Leave empty for no subscriptions

# Path Guidelines:
#   - Use absolute paths for commands
#   - Make sure executables have execute permission
#   - Test tools manually before adding to framework

# Logging Levels:
#   TRACE - Very detailed (development only)
#   DEBUG - Detailed information
#   INFO  - General information (recommended)
#   WARN  - Warnings
#   ERROR - Errors only
#   FATAL - Fatal errors only

# v2.0 New Features:
#   - Integrated Control API - any tool can manage other tools
#   - Interactive console mode (start with -i flag)
#   - No separate control executable needed
#   - Tools can use control_start_tool(), control_stop_tool(), etc.
#   - See docs/CONTROL_API.md for complete reference

# Quick Start:
#   1. Edit this file to add your tools
#   2. Run: ./yuki-frame -c yuki-frame.conf
#   3. Or with console: ./yuki-frame -c yuki-frame.conf -i
#   4. In console: type 'list', 'start tool_name', 'help', etc.
